Vlocity Insurance Group Benefits Enrollment

Make group benefits enrollment a breeze with Vlocity Insurance enrollment features and services.

The Vlocity Insurance enrollment features and services are designed for a wide variety of group benefits enrollment requirements and scenarios:

Enrolling a brand new group of members and their dependents, as a first-time setup for a new company;
Enrolling a new member or members and dependents into existing plans;
Retrieving current enrollment plans, based on a census Id, and allow members to make benefit changes, such as during an open enrollment period;
Allowing members to modify their enrollment, with add, remove, or opt-out features.

TIP: During the initial enrollment period, employees are allowed to waive their rights to coverage for any benefits being offered.

Vlocity can record when an employee opts out of products. To enable this, go to Setup > Company Settings > Data Protection and Privacy, and select the Make data protection details available in records checkbox.

The Vlocity Insurance enrollment and census features are tightly integrated, so you can upload a census into Vlocity, create contact records for the census members, and enroll them into plans.

Here's what it looks like, with the services involved to make it happen:

Small-Group Enrollment Scenarios

Broker Enrollment
A small group broker often provides personalized service for a small business owner or plan administrator by guiding them through rates, product offerings and selections, and the actual enrollment of members.

Enrollment can include taking physical paper forms, entering the data into a formatted file, and uploading the member and plan selection data.

Plan Benefits Administrator
In this scenario, a small group employer is given a secure portal login and makes elections on behalf of their employees as the plan benefits administrator. This could also be performed by a third-party administrator (TPA) hired by the employer and acting on their behalf.

Internal Carrier Representative
A healthcare insurance company can have an internal carrier representative for the small group, who aggregates data and processes for the group.

Member Portal During Open Enrollment
During an open enrollment period, a member logs directly into the member portal and is guided through a process to make elections for their eligible plans.

Enrollment Services
Vlocity has over a dozen enrollment and census-specific services that can be used for enrollment tasks. These are grouped in an OmniScript flow to provide a comprehensive end-to-end enrollment experience.

Product Enrollment Data with a Census
You can upload product enrollment data (medical, dental, vision) with census members, either via OmniScript or spreadsheet.

Add Group Benefits Enrollment Products
Configure the enrollment OmniScript to provide a list of all the available group benefits products.
Add Group Benefits Members and Dependents
Use an Omnistudio Data Mapper as an extract action in the Script Configuration section of the OmniScript structure to extract User, Contact, Account, and Contract IDs for a group benefits member.

Configure the Enrollment Selection Summary for Group Benefits
The Selection Summary section of the enrollment OmniScript structure uses a specific template, Omnistudio Data Mapper, and remote action to configure the completion steps of the group benefits enrollment process.

Enrollment Marketing Events for Group Benefits
During a group benefits enrollment period, you can create marketing events to educate and inform members about new plans and changes to existing plans. For group benefits enrollment, you can request funds for a marketing event by adding an enrollment event to an Account record.

Group Benefits Enrollment Services
There are a number of enrollment-specific services available as part of the InsEnrollmentService class used in group benefits.
